$ PHP code snippets: apache_get_modules
@ apache_get_modules

Return an → development/web/php/snippets/array of loaded → development/Apache/Server/module[apache modules].

If PHP is not running as FPM or fCGI or not in an → development/Apache/Server[Apache] environment, `apache_get_modules()` does not exist. Therefore, the following snippet
checks for the availability of this function with `function_exists`.
code {
if (function_exists('apache_get_modules')) {
  print('<p>apache_get_modules: <br>- ' . join('<br>- ', apache_get_modules()));
}
else {
   print('<p>apache_get_modules() is not defined.;');
}
code }

